Verdict: Lean into the structured job route for now (which aligns with your placement-prep focus). Entrepreneurial/freelance/consulting options open up more credibly in your mid-to-late 20s, once your professional base (and network, via Venus) is established.

Leadership Potential

Moderate-to-good. Saturn (yogakaraka) gives you the discipline and patience leadership requires, but Sun being combust and conjunct Saturn means visible authority will likely come after you've quietly proven competence — you're more "earn it through depth" than "natural spotlight-seeker." Leadership roles after 28–30 look more probable than very early management tracks.

Government Job Potential

There's a real signature here (Sun + Saturn in 10th = classic government/public-sector indicator, and Rahu in the 6th house supports competitive-exam success). But it's not the dominant flavor of this chart — Mercury's strong presence pulls more toward private-sector tech/IT/analytics roles. Practical read: if you're prepping for both PSU/government tech exams and private placements, this chart doesn't discourage either, but the natural pull is toward corporate/private tech.

Foreign Opportunities

This is a genuine strength in your chart. Jupiter (3rd & 6th lord — courage and competition) sits in the 12th house (foreign lands), Ketu sits with it (Ketu naturally signifies the 12th house's themes — distance, foreign settings, research), and Rahu occupies the 6th (competitive/foreign-facing work). Together, this is a meaningful "onsite opportunity / foreign client work / studying or working abroad" signature — worth actively keeping on your radar during placements (e.g., MNCs with global teams, onsite rotation roles), rather than something to wait passively for.
